Check out the comments to see who this weeks winner is...
Keep it up Rockets! You are soaring to new heights!

post_text:
The USDA has extended their FREE feeding program for our students! In order to keep this program at our school, we would love for our families and community members to utilize the program! There is no need to qualify!

Whether you are a family who is part of our Rocket Family, presently enrolled or a community member, we invite you to come and participate!

On Mondays, Ms. Kourtney & the Cafeteria Crew will distribute Breakfasts & Lunches FREE for Mondays, Tuesdays & Wednesdays.

On Wednesdays, Ms. Kourtney & the Cafeteria Crew will distribute Breakfast & Lunches for Thursday & Friday!

Pick up for these meals will be from 8am - 12noon underneath our awning in the drop/off pick up lane!

This is a great opportunity for our families and community members. EVERYONE (18 years and younger) is invited to participate, so don't be shy come and get some good eats! Feel free to share on your social media pages as well!

COMPUTER TIPS & TRICKS!

LOGGING INTO A SCHOOL LAPTOP:
Make sure you are using the email and password that was provided for Clever and that you are connected to your WiFi -- it will not connect correctly if you do not follow these steps.

LOGGING INTO CLEVER:
-Make sure you are using the following website on CHROME: https://clever.com/in/csusa-carolinas
Click on Single-sign on (4 colored squares)
Use the email and password provided on the open house sheet (Make sure to put the ! at the end of the password)
If it's still not working, please clear your browser!

If you need assistance, please email-- SCarbonell@concordlakeacademy.org

Happy Monday!

post_text:
Student Laptop Update:

Hi parents! We have seen a couple of questions come through about logging on to the student laptops that were checked out from school.
At open house you should have received a paper with all of your child's login credentials on it. The top of the paper has our school info and then begins "To the parents of...."
Towards the bottom there is a section titled Schoology/Clever - there you will find your child's email address and their password. That is their Microsoft 0365 login information and can be used to login to the laptop.
Hope this helps!

Dear Rocket Families -
We are currently in the midst of finishing up track selection for our 2020-2021 School Year. The Board of Directors would like all Registered families at this time to make a selection for their 2020-2021 Track, by 3pm on Friday, July 31st. Please visit the Sign Up Genius Below in order to signup for a track. At this time there are a limited number of seats for in-school learning. We can only accept a certain number of students who are face to face based on capacity set by the governor. If you have already signed up for a track, via the survey that was due on July 21st, please do NOT sign up again, as these seats are limited for those who are indeed of signing up still. Thank you so much.

We came across this post and thought it may be helpful to all our new Kinders this upcoming school year!

***Also, please note that if you are coming to CLSA for the first time and have qualified for Free or Reduced Lunches at another school, you will still have to apply for Free & Reduced Lunches at CLSA. Paperwork for this can be found on our website at
www.ConcordLakeAcademy.org
shared_text:
Julie New Harbaugh
August 12, 2019 at 1:14 PM ¬∑

PSA for all soon-to-be kindergarten mamas...
Practice eating ‚Äúschool lunch‚Äù with your kiddo. Make sure they can open everything you send with them. Talk about not eating off of the table in the lunchroom!!! Set a timer for 15 minutes and talk about how they may not finish eating and that‚Äôs ok. (This was HARD for little man.) Practice packing everything back up and talk about what is trash and what should come back home in their lunch box. Kindergarten lunch is a big adjustment and your child‚Äôs teacher will be super appreciative if you have prepared them for the experience!

shared_text:
Concord Lake STEAM Academy
May 7 at 9:35 AM ¬∑

Typically, we have a Kindergarten Promotion, a 5th Grade Promotion, and an 8th Grade Promotion to celebrate the milestones our Scholars have made at Concord Lake STEAM Academy.

This year will be a little different, but we still want to celebrate! If you would like to participate, please submit a Bio and a Picture, of your scholar and about their experiences at Concord Lake STEAM Academy!

Please submit the Bio and Picture in one document in a JPG format to your child's teacher, no later than May 11. Please submit this bio with the understanding that it will be posted to social media and our website.

To learn more visit our website at, www.ConcordLakeAcademy.org

post_text:
Typically, we have a Kindergarten Promotion, a 5th Grade Promotion, and an 8th Grade Promotion to celebrate the milestones our Scholars have made at Concord Lake STEAM Academy.

This year will be a little different, but we still want to celebrate! If you would like to participate, please submit a Bio and a Picture, of your scholar and about their experiences at Concord Lake STEAM Academy!

Please submit the Bio and Picture in one document in a JPG format to your child's teacher, no later than May 11. Please submit this bio with the understanding that it will be posted to social media and our website.

To learn more visit our website at, www.ConcordLakeAcademy.org

To Our Current Rocket Families,
You should have received an email on Monday asking you to update any information in your child's SchoolMint Account. At this time, information needs to be put into SchoolMint by May 29 for the 2020-2021 School Year. Login information was sent to your email on file in PowerSchool in January. This is Phase 2 of your Recommitment to CLSA. Please make sure it is complete. If you need your login information, please email Ms. Jami at jeager@concordlakeacademy.org.
Thank you for your attention to this matter!

Typically, we have a Kindergarten Promotion, a 5th Grade Promotion, and an 8th Grade Promotion to celebrate the milestones our Scholars have made at Concord Lake STEAM Academy.

This year will be a little different, but we still want to celebrate! If you would like to participate, please submit a Bio and a Picture, of your scholar and about their experiences at Concord Lake STEAM Academy!

Please submit the Bio and Picture in one document in a JPG format to your child's teacher, no later than May 11. Please submit this bio with the understanding that it will be posted to social media and our website.

To learn more visit our website at, www.ConcordLakeAcademy.org

CLSA will be hosting a Drive-Thru School Spirit Parade on Thursday, May 7 beginning at 4:00 pm. We invite all families to drive through the drop-off and pick-up line starting at 4pm, to enjoy seeing all your favorite CLSA family staff members. Please feel free to decorate your car with balloons, posters, streamers, and more (painters tape is safe and works great). Following the parade, please make your way to McDonald's drive-thru at 2401 Wonder Drive (behind the school) and get your dinner on! McDonald's is supporting CLSA by helping spread the good word about our school!

To learn more visit our website at, www.ConcordLakeAcademy.org

Concord Lake STEAM Academy
March 27 at 1:42 PM ¬∑

CLSA Parents,
We have a request for you. At this time it is hard to get out in the community for events and visit Preschools, with the COVID-19 Virus. What we are asking is that YOU help spread the word about YOUR school, through your own Social media platforms as well as write reviews for CLSA on Facebook, greatschools.com and on Google. We want to ensure that we are spreading the word that registration is going on now for the 2020-2021 school year. Please feel free to save this image to your computer and share it on your social platforms and use the hashtag #CLSA.
Thank you for your continued support of CLSA during this time.
Ms. Jami

Happy Earth Day! A perspective on the profound importance of nature in times like these from our Lands, Water and Wildlife director, Dan Ritzman:
"This pandemic has changed life as we know it, and for many, it has forced us to take a step back, slow down, and consider what is important. Nature's benefits are undeniable. This Earth Day, it is especially clear that protecting more nature, and creating new ways for people to connect to it, will provide immeasurable benefits." https://www.sierraclub.org/articles/2020/04/lands-and-water-restore-us-we-must-protect-them#

post_text:
Don't miss out on this great opportunity!
THE INVISIBLE BOY WATCH PARTY by Children's Theatre of Charlotte

Tune in April 18 via Facebook or YouTube Live
The watch party will include the opportunity to meet the author and illustrator of the award-winning book along with the cast that helped bring the story to life on stage.

Watch Party Schedule
3:30 p.m. ‚Äì Meet author Trudy Ludwig and illustrator Patrice Barton as they talk about their inspiration for writing this book and field questions from viewers.

4:00 p.m. ‚Äì Watch the musical

5:10 p.m. ‚Äì Meet the adaptors: playwright Chris Parks, composer Josh Totora, director Adam Burke and some of the actors as they discuss the creative process of adapting an award- winning book for the stage.

A message from Trudy Ludwig, author of The Invisible Boy
Not able to attend the watch party on Saturday? The show will be available to stream via our website Monday, April 20 through Friday, April 24.

To Learn More go to: https://tinyurl.com/r5pzr5j
